Parliament, Wednesday, 28 March 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Science and Technology today went through the amendments in the clauses of the National Research Foundation Amendment Bill [ B 23- 2017]. The Chairperson of the Committee, Ms Lindiwe Maseko, thanked the committee for their collective effort in finalising the bill, which has now been formally adopted by the committee. The report will be tabled in the National Assembly. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY, MS LINDIWE MASEKO For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sureshinee Govender Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 2289
